org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.process
Interface IAeProcessWrapperMap

All Known Implementing Classes:
AeProcessWrapperMap
public interface IAeProcessWrapperMap

Defines interface used by persistent process manager to map process ids to process wrappers (which are instances of AeProcessWrapper.

Method Detail

getCurrentWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getCurrentWrapper(long aProcessId)
Returns the current process wrapper for the given process id or null if there is no process wrapper for the given process id. Does not increment the wrapper's reference count the way getWrapper(long) does, so does not require a matching call to releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper). However, this means that successive calls to getCurrentWrapper(long) with the same process id may return different process wrappers.

Parameters:
aProcessId -

getWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getWrapper()
Returns an empty process wrapper. It manufactures a unique id for the map. This call should be followed by a call to set the process id. Each call to getWrapper() or getWrapper(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper).

getWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getWrapper(long aProcessId)
Returns process wrapper for the specified process id. Adds a process wrapper for the process if one does not yet exist. Each call to getWrapper(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper).

Parameters:
aProcessId -

releaseWrapper

public void releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper aWrapper)
Releases a process wrapper allocated by getWrapper(long), if there are no more references to the process.
